Key to the families of Dicotyledons

leads.lead_text: Flowers actinomorphic; calyx and corolla inconspicuous, far exceeded by the stamens; petals valvate in bud; stamens usually many more than 10 (10 only in Prosopis)
Flower zygomorphic to some extent, at least in arrangment of stamens; calyx and corolla conspicuous, nearly as large as or longer than stamens; petals overlapping in bud; stamens 10 or fewer
Corolla not strongly zygomorphic; petals and sepals 5, free; stamens all free, quite exposed
Flower strongly zygomorphic; sepals fused to some extent, the lower 2 petals fused into a keel; stamens usually fused into a partial tube and usually enclosed by keel
